"{\"type\":\"file-history-snapshot\",\"messageId\":\"22ba3f28-8e69-4cdc-a3d8-85cd65ac54db\",\"snapshot\":{\"messageId\":\"22ba3f28-8e69-4cdc-a3d8-85cd65ac54db\",\"trackedFileBackups\":{},\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-25T15:01:06.400Z\"},\"isSnapshotUpdate\":false}\n{\"parentUuid\":null,\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"6527fd86-2c3b-465e-8660-b66ee5ce7da9\",\"version\":\"2.1.47\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"sleepy-soaring-phoenix\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"SessionStart\",\"hookName\":\"SessionStart:clear\",\"command\":\"bash ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/.claude/scripts/remote-setup.sh\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"f8d49720-15ff-4ad2-aa23-98c95e00326e\",\"toolUseID\":\"f8d49720-15ff-4ad2-aa23-98c95e00326e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-25T15:01:06.079Z\",\"uuid\":\"58c1924e-3a96-496e-88e7-5bfe29ceb852\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"58c1924e-3a96-496e-88e7-5bfe29ceb852\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"6527fd86-2c3b-465e-8660-b66ee5ce7da9\",\"version\":\"2.1.47\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"sleepy-soaring-phoenix\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"SessionStart\",\"hookName\":\"SessionStart:clear\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code session-start\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"f8d49720-15ff-4ad2-aa23-98c95e00326e\",\"toolUseID\":\"f8d49720-15ff-4ad2-aa23-98c95e00326e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-25T15:01:06.080Z\",\"uuid\":\"48adb47b-996d-4763-b597-5d85bef7c450\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"48adb47b-996d-4763-b597-5d85bef7c450\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"6527fd86-2c3b-465e-8660-b66ee5ce7da9\",\"version\":\"2.1.47\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"sleepy-soaring-phoenix\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Fix: Git hooks fail in GUI clients (Issue #489)\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nGit hooks installed by `entire enable` use bare `entire` command. GUI git clients (Xcode, Tower, etc.) don't source shell profiles, so `entire` isn't on PATH and hooks fail with `command not found`. The fix adds an opt-in `--absolute-hook-path` flag that embeds the full binary path in git hooks.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. Add `AbsoluteHookPath` setting\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/settings/settings.go`**\\n- Add `AbsoluteHookPath bool` field to `EntireSettings` struct (`json:\\\"absolute_hook_path,omitempty\\\"`)\\n- Add merge logic in `mergeJSON()` (same pattern as `local_dev`)\\n\\n### 2. Add `--absolute-hook-path` flag to `entire enable`\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/setup.go`**\\n- Add `absoluteHookPath` bool flag to `newEnableCmd()`\\n- Pass it through `runEnableInteractive()` and `setupAgentHooksNonInteractive()`\\n- Save to `settings.AbsoluteHookPath`\\n- Pass to `strategy.InstallGitHook()` (new parameter)\\n\\n### 3. Update hook generation to support absolute paths\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/hooks.go`**\\n- Update `hookCmdPrefix(localDev bool)` → `hookCmdPrefix(localDev, absolutePath bool)`\\n- When `absolutePath` is true: resolve via `os.Executable()` + `filepath.EvalSymlinks()`, fall back to `\\\"entire\\\"` on error\\n- Update `InstallGitHook(silent, localDev bool)` → `InstallGitHook(silent, localDev, absolutePath bool)`\\n- Update `isLocalDev()` → add `isAbsoluteHookPath()` helper that reads from settings\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go`** (EnsureSetup)\\n- Update `EnsureSetup()` call to pass `isAbsoluteHookPath()` to `InstallGitHook()`\\n- The existing `!IsGitHookInstalled()` guard means this only fires when hooks are missing — that's fine, we don't need to self-heal stale paths since users can re-run `entire enable`\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/hook_managers.go`**\\n- Update `CheckAndWarnHookManagers()` signature to accept `absolutePath` parameter\\n- Pass through to `hookCmdPrefix()`\\n\\n### 4. Update tests\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/hooks_test.go`**\\n- Update `TestInstallGitHook_LocalDevCommandPrefix` — the `InstallGitHook` calls need the new parameter\\n- Add `TestInstallGitHook_AbsoluteHookPath` — verify hooks contain an absolute path when enabled\\n- Update all other `InstallGitHook()` call sites in tests to pass `false` for the new parameter\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/setup_test.go`** — update any `InstallGitHook` calls if present\\n\\n## Not in scope\\n\\n- Agent hooks (Claude Code, Gemini CLI) — these are invoked by the agent process which has the user's PATH, so they're unaffected\\n- Self-healing of stale absolute paths — users re-run `entire enable` if binary moves\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nManual: `entire enable --absolute-hook-path` then inspect `.git/hooks/prepare-commit-msg` — should contain full path like `/Users/me/.local/bin/entire hooks git prepare-commit-msg ...`\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/soph/.claude/projects/-Users-soph-Work-entire-devenv-cli/ec239294-a815-4fd0-8069-e318bfb4e837.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"22ba3f28-8e69-4cdc-a3d8-85cd65ac54db\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-25T15:01:05.637Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Fix: Git hooks fail in GUI clients (Issue #489)\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nGit hooks installed by `entire enable` use bare `entire` command. GUI git clients (Xcode, Tower, etc.) don't source shell profiles, so `entire` isn't on PATH and hooks fail with `command not found`. The fix adds an opt-in `--absolute-hook-path` flag that embeds the full binary path in git hooks.\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. Add `AbsoluteHookPath` setting\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/settings/settings.go`**\\n- Add `AbsoluteHookPath bool` field to `EntireSettings` struct (`json:\\\"absolute_hook_path,omitempty\\\"`)\\n- Add merge logic in `mergeJSON()` (same pattern as `local_dev`)\\n\\n### 2. Add `--absolute-hook-path` flag to `entire enable`\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/setup.go`**\\n- Add `absoluteHookPath` bool flag to `newEnableCmd()`\\n- Pass it through `runEnableInteractive()` and `setupAgentHooksNonInteractive()`\\n- Save to `settings.AbsoluteHookPath`\\n- Pass to `strategy.InstallGitHook()` (new parameter)\\n\\n### 3. Update hook generation to support absolute paths\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/hooks.go`**\\n- Update `hookCmdPrefix(localDev bool)` → `hookCmdPrefix(localDev, absolutePath bool)`\\n- When `absolutePath` is true: resolve via `os.Executable()` + `filepath.EvalSymlinks()`, fall back to `\\\"entire\\\"` on error\\n- Update `InstallGitHook(silent, localDev bool)` → `InstallGitHook(silent, localDev, absolutePath bool)`\\n- Update `isLocalDev()` → add `isAbsoluteHookPath()` helper that reads from settings\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go`** (EnsureSetup)\\n- Update `EnsureSetup()` call to pass `isAbsoluteHookPath()` to `InstallGitHook()`\\n- The existing `!IsGitHookInstalled()` guard means this only fires when hooks are missing — that's fine, we don't need to self-heal stale paths since users can re-run `entire enable`\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/hook_managers.go`**\\n- Update `CheckAndWarnHookManagers()` signature to accept `absolutePath` parameter\\n- Pass through to `hookCmdPrefix()`\\n\\n### 4. Update tests\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/hooks_test.go`**\\n- Update `TestInstallGitHook_LocalDevCommandPrefix` — the `InstallGitHook` calls need the new parameter\\n- Add `TestInstallGitHook_AbsoluteHookPath` — verify hooks contain an absolute path when enabled\\n- Update all other `InstallGitHook()` call sites in tests to pass `false` for the new parameter\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/setup_test.go`** — update any `InstallGitHook` calls if present\\n\\n## Not in scope\\n\\n- Agent hooks (Claude Code, Gemini CLI) — these are invoked by the agent process which has the user's PATH, so they're unaffected\\n- Self-healing of stale absolute paths — users re-run `entire enable` if binary moves\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nManual: `entire enable --absolute-hook-path` then inspect `.git/hooks/prepare-commit-msg` — should contain full path like `/Users/me/.local/bin/entire hooks git prepare-commit-msg ...`\\n\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"22ba3f28-8e69-4cdc-a3d8-85cd65ac54db\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"6527fd86-2c3b-465e-8660-b66ee5ce7da9\",\"version\":\"2.1.47\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"sleepy-soaring-phoenix\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_014ZMti3uFv5tH9gNZonGWji\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\nI'll implement this plan step by step. Let me start by reading the key files I need to modify.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":14305,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":30008,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":14305},\"output_tokens\":5,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYUzFyziXESnzBrqty754\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"9ac8af84-be5a-4064-9b37-e76e7f94a863\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-25T15:01:10.776Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"9ac8af84-be5a-4064-9b37-e76e7f94a863\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"6527fd86-2c3b-465e-8660-b66ee5ce7da9\",\"version\":\"2.1.47\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"sleepy-soaring-phoenix\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_014ZMti3uFv5tH9gNZonGWji\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01KpCFAoV6ZU749n5Jv6X1gz\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\